The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, May 03, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, May 3, 2004				 																Theatre talk				 																																	A panel discussion on The changes and challenges of English theatre in Calcutta at Oxford Bookstore, at 7 pm. Speakers: Jayant Kripalani, Katy Lai Roy, Ashoke Vishwanathan, Shuktara Lal, Tathagatha Chowdhury and Prithviraj Choudhury. Moderator: Dhruv Mookerjee.				 																Screenings				 																																	Sameera Makhmahlbafs Blackboards will be screened as part of Fringes film festival at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, at 6 pm.				 																																	Citizen Kane and documentaries Film Language and Writing amp; Thinking About Films will be screened at Nandan III, between 11.30 am to 4 pm. By invitation only.				 																Launch				 																																	Indian Journal of World Literature amp; Culture will be launched at American Center, at 3 pm. A panel discussion on Role of Indian scholars in inter-disciplinary approach to literature and culture studies will follow.				 																Science				 																																	Illusions, a science exhibition to mark the 45th anniversary of Birla Industrial amp; Technological Museum, on display on the museum premises.				 																Workshop				 																																	A terracotta workshop for schoolchildren at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, from 10 am to 5 pm. 				 																Art beat				 																																	Terracotta sculptures by Shyamal Roy and Thakurananda Pal on display at Gallery Kanishkas, from 11 am to 8 pm.
